505
00:26:01.059 --> 00:26:02.537
- Fuck me. Naomi.
- I'm sorry.

506
00:26:02.561 --> 00:26:04.247
is this outside of
your comfort zone?

507
00:26:04.271 --> 00:26:06.940
If whacking Mrs. Tiggywinkle
is a bridge too far.

508
00:26:07.065 --> 00:26:09.442
don't worry. there are
plenty of other jobs.

509
00:26:09.568 --> 00:26:12.779
P.S.. that was a bullshit
performance back there.

510
00:26:12.904 --> 00:26:14.507
It's a good thing
we were up against

511
00:26:14.531 --> 00:26:18.201
a sweet old lady. not the
IRG. or we'd both be dead.

512
00:26:19.452 --> 00:26:21.204
[sighs]

513
00:26:21.288 --> 00:26:23.498
Tell me where I fucked up.

514
00:26:26.167 --> 00:26:28.587
You got too close.

515
00:26:30.046 --> 00:26:31.965
Two circles.

516
00:26:32.090 --> 00:26:34.634
One for friends.
one for targets.

517
00:26:34.759 --> 00:26:37.262
They never mix.

518
00:26:37.345 --> 00:26:39.180
A target is an enemy.

519
00:26:39.306 --> 00:26:41.266
That makes Rose's mom an enemy

520
00:26:41.349 --> 00:26:45.270
of you. your country.

521
00:26:45.353 --> 00:26:47.355
of the Agency.

522
00:26:49.149 --> 00:26:52.444
Our enemies shut up. get
out of the way. or die.

523
00:26:52.527 --> 00:26:54.255
[laughs] You should put
that on the website.

524
00:26:54.279 --> 00:26:56.573
Oh. we make sure people know.

525
00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:04.039
♪ Tense. dramatic music ♪

526
00:27:04.122 --> 00:27:06.041
♪♪♪

527
00:27:34.361 --> 00:27:36.655
- [men shouting]
- [gunfire in distance]

528
00:27:45.747 --> 00:27:48.541
[gunfire]

529
00:27:56.174 --> 00:27:58.426
♪♪♪

530
00:28:13.191 --> 00:28:15.485
♪♪♪

531
00:28:30.166 --> 00:28:32.377
♪♪♪

532
00:28:50.228 --> 00:28:52.814
- [door opens]
- [Volchok] Sylviya.

533
00:29:04.826 --> 00:29:06.202
Sylviya.

534
00:29:15.962 --> 00:29:17.255
Ah.

535
00:29:25.054 --> 00:29:27.265
[dogs barking]

536
00:29:32.061 --> 00:29:34.272
♪♪♪

537
00:29:47.494 --> 00:29:49.388
The bulk of the
collection was stolen

538
00:29:49.412 --> 00:29:52.791
during the sack of
Beijing's Old Summer Palace.

539
00:29:52.916 --> 00:29:54.751
Beautiful.

540
00:29:54.834 --> 00:29:57.670
The figures. I mean.

541
00:29:57.754 --> 00:30:00.006
The British looted for a week.

542
00:30:00.131 --> 00:30:03.593
murdering the court.
their children. servants.

543
00:30:03.676 --> 00:30:05.762
Stripped it and set it on fire.

544
00:30:05.845 --> 00:30:07.555
Burned for almost a month.

545
00:30:07.680 --> 00:30:09.974
Ah. the good old days.

546
00:30:11.184 --> 00:30:13.895
The Americans did as you said.

547
00:30:13.978 --> 00:30:15.814
Tried recruiting her.

548
00:30:15.897 --> 00:30:17.982
Did they now?

549
00:30:18.983 --> 00:30:19.859
Well. it's

550
00:30:19.943 --> 00:30:21.027
quite a predicament.

551
00:30:21.152 --> 00:30:23.404
I'm sure your office
will have a view.

552
00:30:23.488 --> 00:30:25.949
The Yanks have
revealed their hand.

553
00:30:26.074 --> 00:30:27.867
Loggerheads. Ugh. horrid word.

554
00:30:27.992 --> 00:30:29.303
Where does it come
from. I wonder?

555
00:30:29.327 --> 00:30:31.371
Well. I-I must dash.

556
00:30:31.454 --> 00:30:34.207
Let's hope there's
a third way. eh?

557
00:30:34.332 --> 00:30:37.627
A mutually beneficial.
longer-term plan for all of us.

558
00:30:41.172 --> 00:30:43.591
Evidence and IDs of
two Russian agents

559
00:30:43.675 --> 00:30:46.094
working in the U.S.
Energy Department.

560
00:30:46.970 --> 00:30:48.697
You must really
want this to happen.

561
00:30:48.721 --> 00:30:51.349
We do have our own ways
of applying pressure.

562
00:30:51.474 --> 00:30:52.851
Oh. I don't doubt it.

563
00:30:52.934 --> 00:30:55.812
But if you're referring
to all that saber-rattling

564
00:30:55.937 --> 00:30:58.565
in the Bab el-Mandeb
Strait. it's not playing.

565
00:30:58.648 --> 00:31:00.900
We thought Guóanbù were
more subtle than that.

566
00:31:00.984 --> 00:31:03.987
- That was nothing to do with us.
- No. of course not. no.

567
00:31:04.112 --> 00:31:06.948
And all this in
there belongs to us.

568
00:31:12.412 --> 00:31:14.539
[Naomi] Martian ask
you to prepare a report

569
00:31:14.622 --> 00:31:15.790
on Samia Zahir?

570
00:31:15.915 --> 00:31:18.376
Yeah. he did. but
not much turned up.

571
00:31:18.459 --> 00:31:20.295
And when did he ask you?

572
00:31:20.420 --> 00:31:21.754
Uh. about two weeks ago.

573
00:31:21.880 --> 00:31:23.548
What was the exact date?

574
00:31:23.673 --> 00:31:25.174
Um...

575
00:31:25.300 --> 00:31:27.844
[typing]

576
00:31:28.803 --> 00:31:31.431
18th April. Uh. morning of.

577
00:31:31.556 --> 00:31:35.059
- Why? Is there a problem?
- [phone ringing]

578
00:31:36.352 --> 00:31:38.229
Um...

579
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:41.458
[British accent] Hello.
Mr. Kent-Jones's office.

580
00:31:41.482 --> 00:31:43.985
[Sami] Hello. this
is Samia Zahir.

581
00:31:44.068 --> 00:31:46.404
I saw Mr. Kent-Jones yesterday

582
00:31:46.529 --> 00:31:49.073
and we agreed to
meet again tomorrow?

583
00:31:49.157 --> 00:31:51.159
Yes. of course. Ms. Zahir.

584
00:31:51.242 --> 00:31:53.578
Uh. let's make you
an appointment.

585
00:31:53.661 --> 00:31:55.914
Uh. does 11 a.m. suit you?

586
00:31:55.997 --> 00:31:57.999
Eleven? Yes.

587
00:31:58.124 --> 00:31:59.804
Brilliant. Uh. we'll
see you tomorrow.

588
00:31:59.834 --> 00:32:02.003
- Thank you.
- [hangs up]

589
00:32:02.086 --> 00:32:04.464
[dials]

590
00:32:04.589 --> 00:32:06.257
[line rings]

591
00:32:06.382 --> 00:32:07.693
[Martian] Simon. what's up?

592
00:32:07.717 --> 00:32:09.445
[regular voice] Hey.
yeah. I got a bite.

593
00:32:09.469 --> 00:32:11.012
Uh. tomorrow. 11 a.m.

594
00:32:11.095 --> 00:32:11.971
Good.

595
00:32:12.055 --> 00:32:14.182
Yeah. She's supposed to...

596
00:32:14.307 --> 00:32:16.684
We need to talk. Now.

597
00:32:16.768 --> 00:32:18.436
[hangs up]

598
00:32:19.604 --> 00:32:21.314
Fuck.

599
00:32:27.362 --> 00:32:28.529
Send someone else.

600
00:32:28.613 --> 00:32:29.989
Why?

601
00:32:30.073 --> 00:32:31.908
You're too close.
You can't see it.

602
00:32:32.033 --> 00:32:34.619
This is routine. She'll come in.

603
00:32:34.702 --> 00:32:37.097
If you don't see it. that is
reason enough to step back.

604
00:32:37.121 --> 00:32:39.681
- You aren't running this. Naomi.
- It's lucky for you I'm not.

605
00:32:39.707 --> 00:32:40.875
Meaning?

606
00:32:41.793 --> 00:32:44.003
Meaning you asked
Simon to run her ID

607
00:32:44.087 --> 00:32:46.506
the day before you
bumped into her.

608
00:32:46.589 --> 00:32:49.676
Simon's mistaken.

609
00:32:50.635 --> 00:32:51.970
Right.

610
00:32:52.053 --> 00:32:54.281
Because it's Simon who's
all over the fucking place.

611
00:32:54.305 --> 00:32:56.557
You are making mistakes
I've never seen you make.

612
00:32:56.641 --> 00:32:58.643
You're not my handler anymore.

613
00:33:00.979 --> 00:33:05.233
No. Because you are no
longer in the field.

614
00:33:05.358 --> 00:33:09.320
You have a nice. cozy desk job.

615
00:33:11.614 --> 00:33:13.658
I have seniority.

616
00:33:15.910 --> 00:33:18.413
Then make the right call.

617
00:33:25.795 --> 00:33:27.755
♪ Low. gloomy music ♪

618
00:33:27.880 --> 00:33:29.424
♪♪♪

619
00:33:31.050 --> 00:33:33.636
[Henry] Say it again.
take your time.

620
00:33:34.887 --> 00:33:37.765
Now. Right.

621
00:33:44.647 --> 00:33:47.525
[whispering] We got a bogie
coming in from Beijing.

622
00:33:48.317 --> 00:33:50.695
We'll bait and switch and see.

623
00:33:59.662 --> 00:34:01.914
Hey. were you part
of that. that walk-in

624
00:34:01.998 --> 00:34:04.125
at the Ecuadorian embassy?

625
00:34:04.250 --> 00:34:05.877
[Henry] Three suitcases guy?

626
00:34:05.960 --> 00:34:07.360
[Bosko laughs] Yeah.

627
00:34:08.212 --> 00:34:09.464
[knock at door]

628
00:34:09.547 --> 00:34:11.299
[door opens]

629
00:34:12.550 --> 00:34:14.469
[Guo] Good morning. gentlemen.

630
00:34:16.094 --> 00:34:19.223
I'm here representing
Dr. Samia Zahir.

631
00:34:19.348 --> 00:34:21.326
I'll be speaking and
acting on her behalf

632
00:34:21.350 --> 00:34:23.186
on all matters from now on.

633
00:34:23.268 --> 00:34:27.065
Okay. Sit down.

634
00:34:33.446 --> 00:34:35.656
[Guo] Your clumsy
recruitment attempt

635
00:34:35.782 --> 00:34:37.468
is endangering a
fragile peace process...

636
00:34:37.492 --> 00:34:40.328
You're in our sphere.
We have protocols.

637
00:34:40.411 --> 00:34:42.663
You shouldn't have
gone behind our backs.

638
00:34:42.789 --> 00:34:44.456
[Guo] Your agency
leaks like a sieve.

639
00:34:44.540 --> 00:34:47.168
You know if either side finds
out about what happened.

640
00:34:47.251 --> 00:34:48.854
they'll put an immediate
stop to the talks.

641
00:34:48.878 --> 00:34:52.340
Oh. so the generals have
not been informed yet?

642
00:34:53.257 --> 00:34:55.318
They'll receive an abridged
version of the facts.

643
00:34:55.342 --> 00:34:57.136
- Ah.
- Routine investigation

644
00:34:57.261 --> 00:34:59.764
has established Dr. Zahir
had been in contact

645
00:34:59.889 --> 00:35:01.974
with a suspected CIA agent.

646
00:35:02.058 --> 00:35:04.310
And thanks to Chinese diligence.

647
00:35:04.393 --> 00:35:07.105
the issue was neutralized
before it became a problem.

648
00:35:07.188 --> 00:35:10.691
As a precaution. Dr. Zahir
will no longer be present

649
00:35:10.817 --> 00:35:13.528
and the negotiations
will now be moved.

650
00:35:13.611 --> 00:35:14.946
[Bosko] Moved?

651
00:35:16.114 --> 00:35:18.449
To where?

652
00:35:18.533 --> 00:35:20.952
- Somewhere else.
- Hmm.

653
00:35:22.328 --> 00:35:24.288
So. what do you expect us to do?

654
00:35:24.372 --> 00:35:26.207
Absolutely nothing.

655
00:35:26.332 --> 00:35:28.376
While you get a
port on the Red Sea.

656
00:35:28.501 --> 00:35:30.545
Divulge the information
that you have.

657
00:35:30.628 --> 00:35:32.147
and there will be
diplomatic consequences.

658
00:35:32.171 --> 00:35:34.632
both public and private.

659
00:35:34.757 --> 00:35:37.385
- [Henry chuckles wryly]
- Okay.

660
00:35:37.468 --> 00:35:41.139
All right. well.
thanks for coming in.

661
00:35:41.264 --> 00:35:43.117
I'm afraid I'm going
to disappoint you

662
00:35:43.141 --> 00:35:47.186
because... I don't give a
rough fuck about diplomacy.

663
00:35:47.270 --> 00:35:49.689
I work in intelligence.

664
00:35:49.814 --> 00:35:53.651
I find it. I create it. I
buy it. and I sell it...

665
00:35:53.776 --> 00:35:58.030
with the Saudis. the Brits.
the Israelis. the whole world.

666
00:35:58.114 --> 00:36:00.783
I bought the phone
that led to Bin Laden.

667
00:36:01.742 --> 00:36:03.578
You want nothing from me?

668
00:36:04.453 --> 00:36:06.747
Nothing has a price.

669
00:36:06.873 --> 00:36:12.128
Nothing is extremely
fucking expensive.

670
00:36:25.975 --> 00:36:28.769
Russians. Two.

671
00:36:28.895 --> 00:36:31.522
Working in the U.S.
Energy Department.

672
00:36:40.239 --> 00:36:42.950
♪♪♪

673
00:36:56.464 --> 00:36:57.965
Sold.

674
00:37:00.301 --> 00:37:03.804
[Martian] The Great
Game. Played by nations.

675
00:37:03.888 --> 00:37:06.933
China. Russia. United States.

676
00:37:07.058 --> 00:37:10.102
Britain. Iran. Saudi Arabia.

677
00:37:10.186 --> 00:37:13.189
A marketplace for
human currency.

678
00:37:13.314 --> 00:37:15.066
We all speculate.

679
00:37:15.149 --> 00:37:17.568
An individual's
price fixed according

680
00:37:17.652 --> 00:37:20.238
to the rise and
fall of the market.

681
00:37:22.823 --> 00:37:24.367
[Robinshaw] You're good.

682
00:37:24.450 --> 00:37:26.911
Your story. I mean.

683
00:37:27.703 --> 00:37:28.983
You never contradicted yourself.

684
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:30.641
You hesitated at
the right times.

685
00:37:30.665 --> 00:37:31.850
You look like you're
telling the truth.

686
00:37:31.874 --> 00:37:33.167
And the machine confirms it.

687
00:37:33.251 --> 00:37:34.460
[monitors beeping steadily]

688
00:37:34.543 --> 00:37:36.921
Question is. do we buy it?

689
00:37:37.004 --> 00:37:39.632
The flat heart rate.
The perfect breathing.

690
00:37:39.757 --> 00:37:41.759
The fake confusion. The sweat.

691
00:37:41.884 --> 00:37:45.680
The "can I have a
glass of water?"

692
00:37:45.763 --> 00:37:49.267
Or are you just a really
talented liar. hmm?

693
00:37:49.350 --> 00:37:52.853
Should we push your talents?

694
00:37:52.937 --> 00:37:55.773
Why is the Agency
interested in this man?

695
00:38:06.909 --> 00:38:08.619
[distant gunfire]

696
00:38:09.745 --> 00:38:11.455
Sylviya.

697
00:39:47.676 --> 00:39:49.637
♪ Tense. ominous music ♪

698
00:39:49.762 --> 00:39:51.597
♪♪♪

699
00:39:51.680 --> 00:39:53.974
[breathing shakily]

700
00:40:24.672 --> 00:40:26.841
[zipping]

701
00:40:35.599 --> 00:40:37.560
Sasha...

702
00:40:37.643 --> 00:40:40.479
[footfalls approach]

703
00:40:45.025 --> 00:40:46.402
[Sasha] Da.

704
00:41:08.257 --> 00:41:09.592
[gasps]

705
00:41:38.454 --> 00:41:41.916
[gunshot]

706
00:41:47.922 --> 00:41:50.049
- [car alarm beeps]
- [Martian] Who called the play?

707
00:41:50.132 --> 00:41:52.092
♪ Tense. atmospheric music ♪

708
00:41:52.218 --> 00:41:54.678
♪♪♪

709
00:41:54.803 --> 00:41:58.182
My friend. when you've lost.

710
00:41:58.307 --> 00:41:59.934
just move on.

711
00:42:00.017 --> 00:42:02.269
Someone told you
how to play this...

712
00:42:03.354 --> 00:42:05.814
and it wasn't Beijing
and it wasn't Khartoum.

713
00:42:05.940 --> 00:42:07.733
Who was it?

714
00:42:07.816 --> 00:42:11.362
I don't know you. but my advice?

715
00:42:12.363 --> 00:42:13.989
Find a new fuck.

716
00:42:14.114 --> 00:42:16.617
I asked you a question.

717
00:42:16.700 --> 00:42:19.203
No one leaves until
you answer it.

718
00:42:20.829 --> 00:42:25.376
Or what? I do anything
here and I'm clean.

719
00:42:25.501 --> 00:42:28.712
You really ready to die for her?

720
00:42:29.588 --> 00:42:31.131
Let's see.

721
00:42:33.884 --> 00:42:36.554
[both grunting]

722
00:42:51.402 --> 00:42:52.403
[yells]

723
00:42:52.486 --> 00:42:54.238
[both grunting]

724
00:43:08.168 --> 00:43:10.170
♪ tense. exciting music ♪

725
00:43:10.296 --> 00:43:12.506
♪♪♪

726
00:43:29.356 --> 00:43:31.483
[panting]

727
00:43:45.080 --> 00:43:47.333
You know. in a 35-year career.

728
00:43:47.416 --> 00:43:49.960
a surgeon will make
17 incorrect decisions

729
00:43:50.044 --> 00:43:51.563
which will have
fatal consequences.

730
00:43:51.587 --> 00:43:54.298
- You didn't make the mistake.
- Maybe not.

731
00:43:54.381 --> 00:43:56.133
Maybe she did.

732
00:43:57.217 --> 00:43:58.427
A woman is dead.

733
00:43:58.510 --> 00:44:01.055
For zero gain.
zero intelligence.

734
00:44:03.057 --> 00:44:07.311
The thing keeping me up tonight
isn't "Did I make a mistake?"

735
00:44:07.394 --> 00:44:10.397
It's "Now I have no line
to get Coyote back."

736
00:44:10.481 --> 00:44:12.858
If we can't. more
people than Sylviya die.

737
00:44:12.941 --> 00:44:14.652
Maybe a lot more.

738
00:44:22.951 --> 00:44:24.495
[speaking Russian]

739
00:44:30.626 --> 00:44:32.836
[man panting]

740
00:44:40.928 --> 00:44:43.472
[grunts]

741
00:44:53.774 --> 00:44:56.068
We are going on a trip.

742
00:44:56.151 --> 00:44:59.613
They say travel
broadens the mind.

743
00:45:01.323 --> 00:45:04.201
These are my best soldiers.

744
00:45:04.326 --> 00:45:08.414
Some of them I found
in prison. Asylums.

745
00:45:08.497 --> 00:45:11.417
Some of them I
wish I never found.

746
00:45:11.500 --> 00:45:15.462
Whenever we stop for a bite
to eat. a bathroom break.

747
00:45:15.587 --> 00:45:19.091
one of them is coming

748
00:45:19.216 --> 00:45:22.094
and getting in with you.

749
00:45:22.177 --> 00:45:24.096
He is locking the door.

750
00:45:24.221 --> 00:45:27.725
and by the time we arrive
to our destination.

751
00:45:27.808 --> 00:45:32.563
your mind. trust me.
will have broadened.

752
00:45:33.605 --> 00:45:36.859
Bon voyage. Coyote.

753
00:45:38.068 --> 00:45:40.112
[soldiers shouting]

754
00:45:40.195 --> 00:45:42.406
[Coyote panting]

755
00:45:50.080 --> 00:45:52.124
♪ driving. percussive music ♪

756
00:45:52.207 --> 00:45:54.418
♪♪♪

757
00:46:07.014 --> 00:46:09.183
♪♪♪

758
00:46:29.661 --> 00:46:31.681
[flight attendant] Mr. Abul-Aziz
Bilal? Would you please

759
00:46:31.705 --> 00:46:33.641
follow me to fill out
the registration forms?

760
00:46:33.665 --> 00:46:35.125
And then you can join Dr. Zahir

761
00:46:35.209 --> 00:46:36.936
- in the lounge afterwards.
- Good evening. Dr. Zahir.

762
00:46:36.960 --> 00:46:38.897
I'm Captain Rogers. Please
follow me through the lounge.

763
00:46:38.921 --> 00:46:40.881
♪ Slow. cerebral music ♪

764
00:46:41.006 --> 00:46:43.133
♪♪♪

765
00:46:47.262 --> 00:46:48.639
[door closes]

766
00:46:49.973 --> 00:46:52.184
Osman will be coming soon.

767
00:46:52.309 --> 00:46:54.895
I want you to come with me now.

768
00:46:57.898 --> 00:47:00.818
I've been ordered
to return home.

769
00:47:00.901 --> 00:47:02.378
They can't force
you to leave London.

770
00:47:02.402 --> 00:47:05.614
Request political asylum.
I'll make sure you get it.

771
00:47:05.697 --> 00:47:08.075
- For what reason?
- Persecution.

772
00:47:08.158 --> 00:47:10.911
Torture. Threat of execution.

773
00:47:11.787 --> 00:47:14.706
Do you know what they do
to traitors' families?

774
00:47:14.790 --> 00:47:17.251
We can work out how to
fix that if you stay.

775
00:47:17.334 --> 00:47:20.504
If you leave. I
can't do anything.

776
00:47:26.176 --> 00:47:29.346
I came to try to
rebuild my country.

777
00:47:31.473 --> 00:47:33.517
That's why I'm here.

778
00:47:36.311 --> 00:47:41.400
Do you think I would
disown my home now?

779
00:47:41.483 --> 00:47:43.151
I would...

780
00:47:44.611 --> 00:47:46.405
I would rather die.

781
00:47:46.530 --> 00:47:48.866
You can't leave.

782
00:47:54.288 --> 00:47:55.998
[whispers] I don't
know who you are.

783
00:47:56.081 --> 00:47:58.792
- Then find out.
- [ragged breaths]

784
00:48:02.004 --> 00:48:04.006
Find out.

785
00:48:30.073 --> 00:48:31.408
Goodbye.

786
00:48:34.578 --> 00:48:35.829
[door opens]

787
00:48:38.498 --> 00:48:40.542
[door closes]

788
00:48:51.219 --> 00:48:53.180
♪ intense music ♪

789
00:48:53.305 --> 00:48:55.432
♪♪♪

790
00:49:07.986 --> 00:49:10.197
♪♪♪

791
00:49:23.627 --> 00:49:25.545
♪ discordant. dramatic music ♪

792
00:49:25.671 --> 00:49:27.923
♪♪♪
